# Admin vs vendor role conflict

Users have a single `users.role` (`admin` | `vendor` | `customer`). An email cannot be both admin and vendor.

## Product policy

- Never demote an admin to vendor via `/sell`.
- Block authenticated admins in `VendorOnboardingController::store` before creating a `VendorApplication`.
- Guests using an admin email get a specific validation error (not “log in and apply again”).
- Pass `isAdminAccount` from `create()` so the SignUp page can hide the form.

## UI pattern on `Vendor/SignUp`

When `isAdminAccount` is true (same pattern as `existingApplication`):

- Hide the application form.
- Show an amber status banner explaining one role per email.
- Tell them to sign out and apply with a **different email**.
- Link to `/admin` for the admin panel.

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD — block and explain
{isAdminAccount ? (
  <div role="status" className="…amber banner…">
    Admin accounts can’t become vendors. Sign out and apply with a different email.
    <a href="/admin">Open admin panel</a>
  </div>
) : existingApplication ? (
  /* existing application banner */
) : (
  <form>…</form>
)}

// ❌ BAD — silently set role to vendor on an admin user
user.update({ role: UserRole::Vendor });
```

## Resolving a stuck local admin who wants to sell

Do not convert the admin user. Create a separate vendor account with another email (or restore `role = admin` in DB/tinker if they were already demoted, then apply with a new email).
